  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Executive / Assistant Manager, Career Conversion Programmes",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p><strong>Programme Administration and Management</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible to oversee the administration of the Career Conversion Programme for hiring employers</li><li>Process, promote, co-ordinate and facilitate grant applications and claims</li><li>Review documentation and identify discrepancies if any</li><li>Generate ad-hoc reports for submission</li><li>Assist with ad-hoc preparation of monthly/quarterly progress updates on CCP for submission to WSG</li><li>Liaise and work with various government agencies, training providers and industry associations</li></ul><p><strong>Programme Marketing and Outreach</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare slides and other relevant marketing materials for engagement with hiring employers</li><li>Identify and maintain a repository of success stories on CCP</li><li>Plan and manage events such as workshops and seminars</li></ul><p><strong>Customer Engagement</strong></p><ul><li>Perform cold calls and make appointments to engage companies including those who write in</li><li>File call reports for networking and engagement sessions and provide the necessary follow-up with enterprises</li><li>Attend to email or phone enquiries</li></ul><p><strong>Claims Processing, Audit and Compliance</strong></p><ul><li>Manage supporting documents submitted, and process for timely claims disbursement</li><li>Adhere to established service standards for processing of processing of applications, claims and enquiries on CCP</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree in any discipline or diploma with at least 2 – 3 years relevant experience</li><li>Preferably with some experience in the administration of government schemes to HR and CEOs of SMEs</li><li>Preferably with some knowledge of government funding schemes for training</li><li>Able to multi-task, comfortable with administrative work and is meticulous</li></ul>",
